               <head>Letters relating to Avadh or Oudh</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018212 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116463 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4089-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled and anonymously compiled collection of letters addressed to several named secretaries, officials, and nobles on subjects relating to the administration of early-nineteenth-century <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2012057976" type="place">Avadh</name> (<name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018147" type="place">Oudh</name>)
                        </p>
                        <p>Several letters mention the date <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1245</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1830</date>, in the reign of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_265857376" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018212" role="pat">Naṣīr al-Dīn Ḥaydar Shāh, King of Oudh</persName>, and other places within the kingdom
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Rough <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">nastaʿlīq</term> in watery ink. Scribe not identified
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
